It was a really hard decision to move from the @basscatboats Cougar to the Puma STS, but I really wanted to give the Puma a try this year.  After a few months, I'm absolutely lovin' the Puma STS.  It's a little larger boat, with a softer ride and bigger deck and still plenty fast.  It's gonna be a hard decision next year because they're both great boats made by a great company....and when paired with the speed and reliability of a @mercurymarine PRO XS - it's just what a tournament angler needs!

Went to visit the cemetery where my Mammaw and Grandad (Rose) were buried in Vanndale, AR today.
While in town, we worshipped at Vanndale Baptist Church beforehand, where I have family and friends. Shed some tears of sadness and joy as I was able to reflect back on some wonderful memories with these two. She was a wonderful woman who loved her family. He was the best fisherman and outdoorsman that most will never hear of. They both loved God, their family, and played a big role in my life. 
They didn’t have much according to the world’s standards but they both lived long happy lives.
See you in heaven Mammaw & Grandad!
“Change your opinions, keep to your principles; change your leaves, but keep intact your roots.”
- Victor Hugo

As we celebrate one of my favorite holiday’s, the verses in 1 Thessalonians 5: 16-18 come to mind. “Rejoice always, pray continually, give thanks in all circumstances, for this is God’s will for you in Christ Jesus”.

I am thankful for so much - Jesus, my family, among many many other people and things…including everyone and everything in the sport of Professional Bass Fishing which has been a big part of my life for over 24 years now….For MLF, BASS, NPFL (and any other Pro trail I might have missed). I should also include ever tournament organization in the world from youth to local, regional and national…the entire sport. 
From the owners, all staff, the anglers, wives, kids, parents, commentators, boat officials & marshals, camera men, writers, announcers/emcees and all media, sponsors, service crews, volunteers, hosts, anglers who have moved on and helped pave the way, all bait and tackle companies, all boat motor and basically any company (endemic & non) that is involved in this sport, and some of the most important - you fans!

Let this verse be a reminder of the blessing of our great sport and to “rejoice”, “pray” and “give thanks” for something so GOOD! 
The closing of the verse says “For this is God’s will”.
That is what He expects of us and inside His will is always the best place to be.
Happy Thanksgiving everyone!

One of the most special phone calls a Christian can receive is when a friend calls and shares that he has been born again…spiritually (John 3:3).
I received such a call a while back from my friend Mark Tucker. I could sense a special peace in his life and could tell that he was very content. 
I roomed with Mark a few times early on at some AAA level events and he was very instrumental in my love for fishing a “finesse jig”. I’ve never met anyone that could fish a little brown jig so methodical and paid so much attention to it’s detail quite like Mark…from the color, weight, amount of skirt strands, how short to bite off the trailer, etc. 
He was a very versatile angler and one of the best jig fisherman the sport has ever known. 
Mark passed recently in his sleep after harvesting this dandy buck. He loved God, his family, and the Outdoors. 
I’ll see you later brother.

Pond owner tip:
I have @mossbackfishhabitat in all sizes all over my lake. I like to leave several of their “root wads” near the bank in shallow areas so kids can catch fish around them.  Placing them where  the top is a couple inches out of the water will help give a visual to cast to, and unlike real wood, they won’t deteriorate and you hardly ever hang up.
